          <strong>Every chess opening lives somewhere in this tree.</strong> Long ago, the world's chess teachers carved every possible first move into a few big families &mdash; flank openings, semi-open games, open games, closed games, Indian defenses. Each family was given a letter (A through E) and a number (00 through 99). Click any branch to open it; click any code at the bottom to play through the games inside.
        </p>

        {ecoTree.map((bucket) => (
          <details class="tree-node">
            <summary set:html={bucket.label}></summary>
